  "response": "Here are some popular and highly-rated project management tools:\n\n1. Asana\n- Great for team collaboration\n- Visual task tracking\n- Free and paid versions\n\n2. Trello\n- Kanban-style boards\n- Intuitive interface\n- Easy to use for small teams\n\n3. Microsoft Project\n- Comprehensive planning\n- Detailed scheduling\n- Best for complex projects\n\n4. Basecamp\n- Simple, clean design\n- Good communication features\n- Flat-rate pricing\n\n5. Jira\n- Popular among software development teams\n- Robust issue tracking\n- Agile project management\n\n6. Monday.com\n- Highly customizable\n- Visually appealing\n- Good for diverse team workflows\n\n7. Notion\n- All-in-one workspace\n- Flexible organization\n- Note-taking and project management\n\n8. ClickUp\n- Versatile features\n- Multiple view options\n- Free plan available\n\n9. Smartsheet\n- Spreadsheet-like interface\n- Resource management\n- Good for larger organizations\n\n10. TeamGantt\n- Gantt chart focused\n- Easy scheduling\n- Visual project timeline\n\nEach tool has unique strengths, so the best choice depends on your specific project needs and team size.",
